{"key":"processedPost-10021286","value":{"id":10021286,"first":10021047,"last":10021443,"when":1237763795,"utime":"03/23/09 02:16 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />i dont see why you wouldn't roll between flushes. <br /></blockquote><br /><br />It's been explained dozens of times why not to roll between flushes.&nbsp; Contaminant spores are naturally going to land on the cake during a flush, where they sit harmlessly, unable to germinate on the fully colonized substrate.&nbsp; If you roll after a flush, the fresh layer of verm protects those contaminant spores and allows them to germinate, contaminating your cakes.&nbsp; As said several times above, only roll after the initial pre-first flush dunk.<br />RR","title":"Re: Lots of conflicting info, trusted cultivators please help!","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}